questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot 3.2 application deployed on JDK 21 exhibits severe performance degradation under high concurrent load. The application utilizes Virtual Threads (`Executors.newVirtualThreadPerTaskExecutor()`) to process incoming HTTP requests. A thread dump reveals that many platform carrier threads are in `BLOCKED` states, and CPU utilization is unusually low despite high response latencies. You locate the following service implementation:

java
@Service
public class PaymentProcessingService {
    private final PaymentGatewayClient gatewayClient;

    public PaymentProcessingService(PaymentGatewayClient gatewayClient) {
        this.gatewayClient = gatewayClient;
    }

    public synchronized PaymentResult processPayment(PaymentRequest request) {
        // Heavy external HTTP call to a legacy payment provider
        return gatewayClient.executeHttpCall(request);
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application processes financial transactions. A service method marked with `@Transactional` initiates an asynchronous task using `CompletableFuture.supplyAsync` to perform a parallel audit log. Developers report that the audit log occasionally fails to write to the database, or writes with missing context, and database connection pool exhaustion is frequently observed under peak load. 

java
@Transactional
public void completeOrder(Order order) {
    orderRepository.save(order);
    CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
        auditService.logTransaction(order.getId(), "COMPLETED");
    }, customExecutor);
}
